        <figure class="stats-bar-image">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/36262564/pexels-photo-36262564.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1000" alt="LAX air traffic control tower silhouetted against a stunning sunset sky" width="1000" height="666""lazy">
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LEDE (v7: with side image) -->
  <section class="lede-section lede-section--with-image">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="lede-grid">
        <div class="lede-text-col">
        <p class="lede">Stairway Mortgage qualifies air traffic controllers on the income they actually earn — <strong>locality pay included, premium pay counted, facility-upgrade trajectory factored in</strong>. A developmental at OKC, a CPC at a Level 8 tower, a Level 12 en-route controller at ZNY, a TMC, a supervisor, and a pre-retirement controller planning around the age-56 mandatory exit each get qualified using the income method that fits their position on the federal pay scale.</p>
        </div>

        <figure class="lede-image">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/17220618/pexels-photo-17220618.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=900" alt="Close-up architectural detail of an airport control tower" width="900" height="600""lazy">
          <figcaption class="lede-image-caption">Real federal pay. Real career arc. Real underwriting.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- KEY HIGHLIGHTS -->
  <section class="highlights-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header highlights-intro">
        <div class="eyebrow">Key Facts &amp; Highlights</div>
        <h2>Key facts every air traffic controller should know about home loans.</h2>
        <p>Each point below is sourced from federal, regulatory, or industry authorities. Verify any of them directly through the linked references.</p>
      </div>

      <ul class="highlights-list">
        <li>Air traffic controllers qualify for a mortgage using federal GS pay tables plus their facility locality factor from day one of employment. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/pay-leave/salaries-wages" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OPM locality pay used in air traffic controller mortgage qualifying</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Locality pay ranges from 16% (rest of U.S.) to 45%+ (San Francisco) — and must be counted toward ATC mortgage qualification. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/pay-leave/salaries-wages/salary-tables/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OPM locality pay area definitions used in air traffic controller mortgage qualifying</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Sunday premium pay (25% of base), night differential (10%), and holiday pay (2x) all qualify under Method 2 income. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.consumerfinance.gov/rules-policy/regulations/1026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CFPB Regulation Z qualified-mortgage rules</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Controller Incentive Pay (CIP) at high-traffic facilities adds $5,000-$20,000+ annually and counts toward qualifying. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.faa.gov/about/office_org/headquarters_offices/ato" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FAA ATO context for the air traffic controller mortgage</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Level 10-12 controllers at busy facilities (ZNY, ZAU, ZTL, A80, N90) routinely qualify for jumbo loan programs. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.fhfa.gov/data/conforming-loan-limit-cll-values" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FHFA conforming loan limits for the air traffic controller mortgage</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Federal mandatory retirement at age 56 for ATCs requires specific mortgage amortization planning. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.law.cornell.edu/uscode/text/5/8425" target="_blank" rel="noopener">5 USC 8425 retirement law affecting the air traffic controller mortgage</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Military-trained ATCs retain full VA home loan benefits when transitioning to FAA employment. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.va.gov/housing-assistance/home-loans/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">VA loan as an air traffic controller mortgage option</a>)</span></li>
        <li>NATCA represents nearly 20,000 air traffic controllers and other FAA professionals. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.natca.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NATCA union</a>)</span></li>
        <li>TSP (Thrift Savings Plan) balances can qualify as asset-based mortgage income for pre-retirement controllers. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.tsp.gov" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Thrift Savings Plan</a>)</span></li>
        <li>FAA Academy training at Oklahoma City is the entry point to controller employment and pay scale. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.faa.gov/about/office_org/headquarters_offices/ang/offices/tc" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FAA Academy training reference</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Future-rate income qualification covers documented facility upgrades (Level 7 to Level 12 can add $40-80K annually). <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://guide.freddiemac.com/app/guide/section/5303.4" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Freddie Mac variable income guidelines</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Federal Employees Retirement System (FERS) pension counts at full value as retirement-age qualifying income. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.opm.gov/retirement-services/fers-information/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OPM FERS information</a>)</span></li>
        <li>BLS data shows air traffic controllers among the highest-paid federal employees by occupation. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.bls.gov/ooh/transportation-and-material-moving/air-traffic-controllers.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BLS air traffic controller wage data</a>)</span></li>
        <li>Mortgage interest deduction caps apply to controller home purchases just like other federal employees. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.irs.gov/publications/p936" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IRS Publication 936</a>)</span></li>
        <li>NMLS Consumer Access verifies licensing for every loan originator working on your loan. <span class="highlights-source">(<a href="https://www.nmlsconsumeraccess.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NMLS Consumer Access lookup</a>)</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- WHO THIS PAGE IS FOR -->
  <section class="section section-tinted">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <div class="eyebrow">01 · Who this page is for</div>
        <h2>Air traffic controller mortgage scenarios from training through retirement.</h2>
        <p>Developmental at the Academy. CPC at a Level 7 tower. Level 12 en-route. Supervisor. Pre-retirement. Each gets qualified on the right number for their stage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="audience-portrait-strip">
        <figure class="audience-portrait">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/12257586/pexels-photo-12257586.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=700" alt="Schiphol airport control tower with active ground operations" width="600" height="750" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x750/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=Approach+Control';">
          <figcaption class="audience-portrait-caption">Approach / regional tower</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="audience-portrait">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/33404486/pexels-photo-33404486.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=700" alt="Iconic modern air traffic control tower at Istanbul Airport" width="600" height="750" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x750/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=Tower+Control';">
          <figcaption class="audience-portrait-caption">Major-hub tower (Level 10–12)</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="audience-portrait">
          <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/18949825/pexels-photo-18949825.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=700" alt="Sleek modern air traffic control tower at Belgrade airport" width="600" height="750" loading="lazy" onerror="this.onerror=null;this.src='https://placehold.co/600x750/0A0E1A/E8EEFF/png?text=Center+Facility';">
          <figcaption class="audience-portrait-caption">En-route center facility</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Career stage</th>
            <th>Typical pay (2026)</th>
            <th>Where the qualifying complexity is</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Developmental at Academy (OKC)</td>
